<subSubSection id="C30F0386B13BFF9EFF55FEA5FB9CF897" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB13BFF9EFF55FEA5FC47FE62" blockId="14.[166,1225,319,474]" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">
R e m a r k s. This specimen shows several characters supplementary to the redescription in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF842DFCB13BFF9EFF72FE85FD94FEC2" author="Korneyev, V. A." box="[252,530,351,378]" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" pagination="115 - 130" refId="ref10675" refString="Korneyev, V. A. A revision of Afrotropical species of the Eupyrgota (Diptera, Pyrgotidae): the varipennis and melancholica subgroups of species // Vestnik zoologii. - 2006 b. - 40, N 2. - P. 115 - 130." type="book chapter" year="2006">Korneyev (2006 b: 124)</bibRefCitation>
: parafacial dark brown to black, usually with yellow spot at level of antennal base, shining, often wrinkled (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13BFF9EFD5AFE9AFC94FE22" box="[724,786,383,410]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[166,199,1721,1743]" captionTargetBox="[190,1222,602,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-128@14.[166,1231,602,1679]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Eupyrgota vespiformis, ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–4 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — left anterior; 4 — dorsal); 5 — wing; 6–7 — abdomen (6 — left; 7— dorsal)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403947/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">fig. 7</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13BFF9EFC90FE9AFCCFFE21" box="[798,841,383,409]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13BFF9EFC90FE9AFCA8FE21" box="[798,814,383,409]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[166,199,1357,1379]" captionTargetBox="[196,1203,181,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-176@6.[196,1203,174,1356]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig.2. Eupyrgota alienata, holotype ♀ (BMNH) (1–2) and non-type ♀ (NHMB) (3–6): 1 — habitus, dorsal; 2 — labels; 3–4 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior); 5 — wing; 6 — fore coxa. Рис. 2. Eupyrgota alienata, голотип ♀ (BMNH) (1–2) и нетиповая ♀ (NHMB) (3–6): 1 — общий вид, дорсально; 2 — этикетки; 3–4 — голова (3 — слева; 4 — спереди); 5 — крыло; 6 — передний тазик." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403935/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13BFF9EFCB5FE9AFCCFFE21" box="[827,841,383,409]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[176,209,1342,1364]" captionTargetBox="[194,1203,178,1317]" captionTargetId="figure-181@7.[194,1204,174,1318]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — wing; 7 — mid femur and tibia, anterior; 8 — abdomen, left. Рис. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, голотип ♀ (BMNH): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2 — этикетки; 3–5 — голова (3 — слева;4 — спереди;5 — дорсально); 6 — крыло; 7 — среднее бедро и голень, спереди;8 — брюшко,слева." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403937" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403937/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">3</figureCitation>
</emphasis>
); fronto-orbital plates very wide and shining, smooth or wrinkled, as wide as or wider than matt frontal vitta (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13BFF9EFBD5FE7AFB1DFE02" box="[1115,1179,415,442]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[166,199,1721,1743]" captionTargetBox="[190,1222,602,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-128@14.[166,1231,602,1679]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Eupyrgota vespiformis, ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–4 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — left anterior; 4 — dorsal); 5 — wing; 6–7 — abdomen (6 — left; 7— dorsal)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403947/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">fig. 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13BFF9EFB24FE7AFB3EFE01" box="[1194,1208,415,441]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1641,1663]" captionTargetBox="[263,1145,180,1601]" captionTargetId="figure-5@9.[191,1208,174,1626]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Eupyrgota armipes, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur and tibia, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior view; 8 — fore trochanter; 9 — mid trochanter; 10 — wing; 11 — mesonotum and abdomen, dorsally; 12 — abdomen, posterior." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403939/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13BFF9EFB24FE7AFB3EFE01" box="[1194,1208,415,441]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">4</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
); eversible membrane half as long as dorsal side of oviscape (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13BFF9EFCD4FE5AFC11FE62" box="[858,919,447,474]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[166,199,1721,1743]" captionTargetBox="[190,1222,602,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-128@14.[166,1231,602,1679]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Eupyrgota vespiformis, ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–4 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — left anterior; 4 — dorsal); 5 — wing; 6–7 — abdomen (6 — left; 7— dorsal)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403947/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">fig. 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13BFF9EFC2DFE5AFC37FE61" box="[931,945,447,473]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[166,199,1666,1688]" captionTargetBox="[220,1195,215,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-8@12.[188,1210,206,1590]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., holotype ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–5 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — anterior; 4 — left; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior; 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, ventral. Рис. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., голотип ♀ (NMKE): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2–5 — голова (2 — спереди слева;3 — спереди; 4 — слева;5 — дорсально); 6 — переднее бедро,вид сзади;7 — среднее бедро, спереди; 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко, вентрально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403943" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403943/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13BFF9EFC2DFE5AFC37FE61" box="[931,945,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">6</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6A0085B13BFF9EFF28F95CFD7DF952" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403947" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6403947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403947/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" startId="14.[166,199,1721,1743]" targetBox="[190,1222,602,1675]" targetPageId="14">
